The paper deals with hyperspectral image analysis, specifically hyperspectral image classification, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of neural networks (cs.LG) and hierarchical methods, which are often used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of time-frequency methods (cs.NE) and Fourier transforms, which are commonly used in signal processing and image analysis (cs.IR).
